If the plaintiff demanded a debt before it was due, he would not only lose his case in that action, but could not bring action again, quod ea res in iudicium ante venisset. The reservation‚ cuius pecuniae dies fuisset, was a technical qualification of his claim that saved him from being bari-ed in a subsequent action.
